@yelrahkcorb NP, long as you're not being cheeky, lol. I mean, someone needs to say something, all that's ever talked about is female oppression, and how they're victims, and somehow 'invisible' despite the fact that they're the only ones ever talked about.. 

I'm not a misogynist, and will easily call out anyone that is, objectively so. But, I really am tired of the hypocrisy and imbalance in representation.. 

According to a campaign by shoppers drug mart, women's health is "invisible".. well, then explain why men are the ones overwhelmingly dying sooner than women..? I mean, I'm no biologist or anything, but I'd say living longer is a pretty huge factor when it comes to health..

@yelrahkcorb Yea, the censorship is real. I've had 2 full multi-paragraph messages deleted on this thread alone.. 

There's this whole mentality going around that if you can't say what you gotta say within 2 sentences, then it ain't worth saying. But I say, if you can't articulate more than two sentences, then you ain't worth listening to. At least in terms of being argumentative. 

I mean, there's zero sense in adding arbitrary conflict with zero points that anyone can learn from. It's all this right vs left, good vs bad, shit; that just dilutes all the mainstream conversation. But it's all binary nonsense that doesn't take the bigger picture into account. It only ever focuses on the symptoms but never the causes, and only ever focuses on what's popular, but rarely what is factual.

